wiki.text:
'CDFS' may refer to:
* CDfs, a Linux virtual file system. ** Similar Plan 9 program running under the
  "cdfs" name is also covered by the article.
* ISO 9660, the common CD file system, a number of operating systems refer to
  this as CDFS.
* cdfs.sys (CD-ROM File System Driver), the CD file system driver for Windows
  platforms.
* the Chandra Deep Field South, a region of the sky where the deepest
  astronomical observations by the Chandra X-ray Observatory have been made.
